&lt;p&gt;Thanks for Sharing Matt :) &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You can also use Google Tag Manager and a dataLayer to capture events and then it can be pushed upstack to Google Analytics and / or any other tools, just as easy:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;dataLayer.push(&#123;&#039;event&#039;:&#039;myEvent&#039;,&#039;eventCategory&#039;:&#039;ABC&#039;,&#039;eventAction&#039;:&#039;DEF&#039;,&#039;eventLabel&#039;:&#039;GHI&#039;&#125;);&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The other thing to consider is using Custom Dimensions to enrich your events, for example, with a User Id (to identify the user), the Client Id (the internal Analytics Id) or other attributes, for example whether its a blog page, product page etc. Custom Metrics can be used to capture if its a Brochure Download, Sign In, Video View, Feature Request.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The nice thing about capturing a Client Id and / or User Id is you can then use the Measurement Protocol to embed follow on hits which may take place within an app or offline process :)&lt;/p&gt;
